placed Megan in Hufflepuff House.[4] She shared a dormitory in the Hufflepuff Basement with Hannah Abbott and Susan Bones.  Behind the scenes The Unidentified female Hufflepuff student from the films may represent her, as may the Potions Club girl. Appearances Harry Potter and Me (First mentioned) Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix (film) (Possible appearance) Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince (video game) (Possible appearance) Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2 (Possible appearance) Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2 (video game) (Possible appearance) LEGO Harry Potter: Years 5-7 Pottermore Notes and references   ↑ She started Hogwarts in the 1991-1992 school year. In Britain, you have to be 11 by the 1 September of the respective year and turn 12 in or by 31 August the next year, to be in a certain year group. Megan has to be born in that period in either 1979 or 1980 to start Hogwarts by September 1991.  ↑ Harry Potter and Me  ↑ "World Exclusive Interview with J K Rowling," South West News Service, 8 July 2000  - "Hogwarts just serves Britain and Ireland."  ↑ 4.0 4.1  Pottermore              Categories         Categories:   20th century births    British or Irish individuals    Females    Half-bloods    Hufflepuffs    Hufflepuffs Sorted in 1991    Jones family    Wizards             Languages      Deutsch Español Français Polski Русский      *Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links, meaning, at no additional cost to you, Fandom will earn a commission if you click through and make a purchase. Community content is available under CC-BY-SA unless otherwise noted.             Advertisement     Fan Feed        More Harry Potter Wiki     1 Sirius Black     2 Hufflepuff     3 Ravenclaw                           Explore Wikis            Universal Conquest Wiki        Let's Go Luna! Wiki        Club 57 Wiki                              Explore properties          Fandom               Cortex RPG               Muthead         